genresAdvancedInfo.name: trad quebecois
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre of music hails from the French-speaking province of Quebec, Canada and is deeply rooted in the region's history and culture. It features traditional instruments such as the fiddle, accordion, and foot percussion, and often tells stories of rural life and the struggles of the working class. The music is characterized by its lively and energetic sound, and its ability to bring people together in celebration and community.
